DSL uses telephone lines to provide internet access.

Pros:

Affordable

Widely available

Does not tie up phone line

Cons:

Slower than broadband and fiber

Speed depends on distance from provider

Not suitable for heavy usage

(D) Satellite Internet

Description:
Satellite internet uses satellites orbiting the Earth to provide connectivity.

Pros:

Available in remote and rural areas

No need for cables or infrastructure

Wide coverage

Cons:

High latency (delay)

Expensive plans and equipment

Affected by weather conditions

(E) Mobile Data (3G/4G/5G)

Description:
Internet provided through cellular networks using SIM cards.

Pros:

Portable and wireless

Easy to set up

Available almost everywhere

Cons:

Limited data plans

Speed varies with signal strength

Can be expensive for heavy usage

